m_q.target_metric: RMSE between predicted and observed Swarm Alpha atmospheric density values over the 4-hour forecast window
filters: Training data from wu334 (OMNI/GOES: 2016-10-22 to 2016-10-23; Density: 2016-10-23 to 2016-10-24)
Evaluation data from wu335 (OMNI/GOES: 2016-10-25 to 2016-10-26; Density: 2016-10-29)
sub_questions: Train a VAR(1) model using a 16-hour context window of OMNI2 (f10.7_index, Kp_index, Dst_index_nT) and GOES (xrsb_flux_observed, xrsa_flux_observed) variables to project the time series forward.
Fit a linear regression model to predict the next 4 hours of Swarm Alpha's atmospheric density.
Calculate the RMSE between the predicted and observed density values for the evaluation dataset.

constraints: The 16-hour context window must contain valid data.
The 4-hour forecast window must contain valid data.
derived_filters: Training data: Timestamp between 2016-10-22 00:00:00 and 2016-10-23 23:00:00 for OMNI2 and GOES, and 2016-10-23 00:00:00 and 2016-10-24 03:00:00 for Swarm Alpha density.
Evaluation data: Timestamp between 2016-10-25 00:00:00 and 2016-10-26 23:00:00 for OMNI2 and GOES, and 2016-10-29 00:00:00 and 2016-10-29 03:00:00 for Swarm Alpha density.
output_format_requirements: Report the RMSE value with appropriate units.
